2. DEFINING THE CONDITION: EXECUTIVE SCOPE INFLATION DISORDER (ESID)

Executive Scope Inflation Disorder (ESID) is characterized by:
	1.	The belief that scaling parameters equals scaling wisdom.
	2.	The assumption that training on text about war equals understanding war.
	3.	The conviction that proximity to GPUs confers moral authority.
	4.	A compulsive need to mention “AGI” in unrelated contexts.

Diagnostic Criteria

An SVTS may be diagnosed with ESID if they:
	•	Reference “autonomous drone swarms” within 90 seconds of discussing a chatbot.
	•	Invoke constitutional amendments while selling API credits.
	•	Describe their company as “standing at the threshold of superintelligence” while the model cannot reliably sort grocery items alphabetically.
	•	Frame enterprise licensing decisions as acts of civilizational heroism.

Left untreated, ESID progresses into Advanced Messiah Founder Complex (AMFC), in which the CEO perceives themselves as the final moral checkpoint before Skynet.

