5. THE FOURTH AMENDMENT AMPLIFICATION LOOP (FAAL)

The FAAL occurs when an SVTS claims that LLMs threaten constitutional protections by enabling mass surveillance.

Operational reality:

An LLM:
	•	Cannot deploy microphones.
	•	Cannot independently collect data.
	•	Cannot operate without external provisioned inputs.
	•	Cannot execute legal authority.
	•	Cannot autonomously surveil.

It processes text supplied to it.

Mass surveillance infrastructure, where it exists, is a function of:
	•	Sensor networks
	•	Storage architectures
	•	Collection policy
	•	Legal frameworks
	•	Institutional actors

The model does not initiate constitutional violation.

It summarizes.

